entry.title: [sync] Always use PASSWORDS in transport mode if local UPM pref is "on"
entry.content:
No behavior change because the pref is always "off" so far.

- Convert kPasswordsUseUPMLocalAndSeparateStores from a boolean pref to

an integer pref with 3 possible values: "on", "off" and

"off-and-migration-pending". No pref migration is required because

the pref was never written.

- In the "on" state, always configure the passwords controller in

SyncMode::kTransportOnly, even for syncing users.

- In the "off-and-migration-pending" state, suppress password sync.

entry.title: [css-variables] Count “--foo: initial” as a style declaration.
entry.content:
When the current system of independent inheritance-like behavior

for custom properties was written, the ComputedStyle was marked as

having a variable declaration from fairly deep down in Resolve().

However, if using “initial” (or “inherit”, but that should be

irrelevant for this discussion), Resolve() would never be called,

and the ComputedStyle would erroneously be counted as not having

a variable declaration. Thus, independent inheritance would not

be properly stopped for such elements, leading to wrong results

in some recalcs.



Fix by setting the property in CustomProperty::Apply* instead,

which seems like a more logical place to begin with. (We could

also apply it in StyleBuilder::ApplyPhysicalProperty() if we

wish to have it only one place, but it would require an extra

test there that would be irrelevant for most properties.)

entry.title: Missing ::first-letter style update for size queries
entry.content:
Style for ::first-letter pseudo elements are updated as late as possible

to allow nodes to re-attach to make sure any first-letter text node

changes are included when computing style for the first rendered letter.



When the StyleRecalcChange were already marked for ReattachLayoutTree()

when reaching the ::first-letter update, we assumed some ancestor of the

::first-letter element would be re-attached, and the ::first-letter

style being updated in Element::AttachLayoutTree() for the originating

element. But, if the originating element was a size container, and we

skipped style recalc for its descendants, we would mark the stored

StyleRecalcChange for re-attachment of the children when resuming, even

if the originating element itself would be re-attached.



Instead, check that we also did not suppress style recalc for the

originating element for the ::first-letter before skipping its style

update during style recalc.



Bug: 1505250

entry.title: [mullet m3] Add PopupType::kAutocomplete for popup showing autocomplete.
entry.content:
PopupType is computed based on the passed form, field and triggering

source. Autocomplete suggestions are shown when we can't generate other

suggestion types. The PopupType is not updated in AED in this case.

This means that AED::GetPopupType() can return arbitrary value when

autocomplete suggestions are shown.



This CL adds a dedicated PopupType::kAutocomplete to be used when

autocomplete suggestions are shown. This requires updating all places

where PopupType is used:



* ChromeAutofillClient::ShowAutofillSettings - can't be called when AC

suggestions are shown -> no changes required.

* suggestions_list_metrics::LogAutofillSelectedManageEntry - can't be

logged when AC suggestions are shown -> no changes required.

* popup_cell_utils::FormatLabel - can be called when AC suggestions

are shown -> add formatting for autocomplete suggestion labels.

* FormInputAccessoryViewController::announceVoiceOverMessageIfNeeded -

uses different AX labels - add new autocomplete AX label.

* CreditCardAutofillTouchBarController::initWithController - has special

logic for credit card popup type - no changes required for autocomplete.



Next steps: override PopupType in AED when autocomplete suggestions are

shown.

entry.title: Track animating compositors in OcclusionTrackerPauser
entry.content:
Currently, OcclusionTrackerPauser always hits the timeout if there is an

external monitor attached. The reason it happens on an external display

is because the OcclusionTrackerPauser requires a non-animated frame to

be pushed for each display before it will unpause. If there is only one

display, and the precondition that an animation is running when calling

PauseUntilAnimationsEnd is true, then this will work. But, with multiple

displays, there may not be animations running on all displays, so some

displays will not push any frame at all, leaving it to wait forever.

This CL bookkeeps which compositors are animating and unpauses when

there are no animating compositors left.

entry.title: Allow DevTools intercept fetch keepalive requests after migration
entry.content:
1. The Chromium DevTools Protocol allows developer to intercept

network requests by calling `Network.setRequestInterception` [1]

API. This is achieved by intercepting a URLLoaderFactory mojo

by adding a proxy between a remote/receiver pair (See [2]).



However, after in-browser migration, the URLLoaderFactory

implementation used by fetch keepalive requests will not be

the default one for other subresources, such that it cannot be

updated by the browser -> renderer mojo call

`SubresourceLoaderUpdater::UpdateSubresourceLoaderFactories()`.



This CL supports such URLLoaderFactory update from RFHI via

KeepAliveURLLoaderService::FactoryContext, without going back

to renderer.



Example failure without this CL: [3]



2. This CL also fixes the issue that fetch keepalive requests stop

working after network service crashes. The service is also created

via `RenderFrameHostImpl::UpdateSubresourceLoaderFactories()`, which

will be able to update KeepAliveURLLoaderService via its

FactoryContext.



[1]: https://chromedevtools.github.io/devtools-protocol/tot/Network/#method-setRequestInterception

[2]: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:content/browser/devtools/devtools_url_loader_interceptor.cc;l=759;drc=8e78783dc1f7007bad46d657c9f332614e240fd8

[3]: https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/try/linux-rel/1625058/test-results?sortby=&groupby=

entry.title: Add metrics for compose dialog consent flows
entry.content:
This CL logically separates a compose "consent session" from a "main session" for metrics purposes. ComposeSessions begin when a dialog is created. Compose "consent sessions" end when the dialog advances past the consent/disclaimer UI to the main UI state, or when the dialog is closed via close button or rejection of consent.



In the former case, we will log two separate sets of metrics: one for the dialog in its consent UI state, and one for the dialog in its main UI state. In this way we keep logged information about the consent dialog separate from existing metrics.



This CL introduces the following metrics for the above purposes

Compose.Session.DialogShownCountConsent.Accepted and Compose.Session.DialogShownCountConsent.Ignored

- Track the number of shows of the dialog for a compose consent session. Split by whether the session ends "Accepted" (consent was given or disclaimer was acknolwedged) or "Ignored" (consent was denied or x button closed)

Compose.Session.Consent.CloseReason

- The ways in which the consent session is exited. This includes both ending session lifetime by closing the dialog, and ending just the consent portion of the session by advancing to the dialog's main UI state. In the latter case, we also split by whether or not the main session ended with an inserted suggestion.

Compose.Session.Consent.GivenInSession

- As documented

entry.title: Fix the broken tests when AppStorage is enabled(Part 5).
entry.content:
When the kAppServiceStorage flag is enabled, AppService blocks the

app publishers creating until it's ready, after reading from the

AppStorage file. This affects some tests:



1. BorealisContextTest.*.

Because BorealisServiceFake is created when BorealisApps publisher is

created, and tests use BorealisServiceFake which reports CHECK error

due to no BorealisFeatures setting.



2. BorealisInstallUrlHandlerTest.*.

Because BorealisServiceFake is created when BorealisApps publisher is

created, and tests use BorealisServiceFake which reports CHECK error

due to no BorealisWindowManager setting.



2. BorealisShutdownMonitorTest.*.

Because BorealisServiceFake is created when BorealisApps publisher is

created, and tests use BorealisServiceFake which reports CHECK error

due to no BorealisWindowManager setting.



Modify Borealis's tests to set BorealisFeatures, BorealisWindowManager

for BorealisServiceFake in tests.
